<seg id=1> Huang Sihua: Build Favorable Environment Next Year, Malaysia Wants to Retain 10B Foreign Stock Investment </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Kuala Lumpur) Huang Sihua, Vice Finance Minister of Malaysia, said it was expected that foreign investment of over 10 billion Ringits might be withdrawn from the stock market on September 1st next year, when foreign exchange controls had been carried out for one full year. He stated that the government would take steps to build a favorable investment environment to encourage foreign capital to stay in Malaysia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said that according to the economic growth rate in Q3, Malaysia's economy was reviving. It was believed that by next September the economy would become stable, market activities would have resume, and foreign investors would decide to invest in Malaysia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Huang Sihua gave a speech at the Chinese Business Association of Malaysia Economic Reporting and Communication Meeting the day before yesterday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He emphasized that Malaysia determined the exchange rate to be 1 USD to 3.8 Ringits, which would allow investors to plan long term investments, make more exact decisions, and worry less about the fluctuation of currency. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He said that the regulatory steps would last for some time until the international currency market becomes stable. A system to regulate gambling activities as well as create transparent transactions was set up and maintained, to avoid the financial storm expected to hit South and East Asian regions once more. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> On the other hand, Huang Sihua said that 20% of companies that have previously applied for loans, but had been refused, had now been approved all over the country. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> He said that Finance Ministry would continue to provide consulting or related assistance for companies that applied for loans but had been initially refused, to allow companies that wanted realization of their development plans follow their plan successfully and promote domestic market activities. </seg>
</p>
